ferc_filing_data.tariff_title: Fountain Valley Power, L.L.C., Rate Schedules

record_data.record_plain_text: Fountain Valley Power, L.L.C. Rate Schedule for Provision of Emergency Power Pursuant to Interconnection Agreement Obligations Fountain Valley Power, L.L.C. (“Fountain Valley Power”), will provide real power produced by its natural gas-filed generating facility (the “Fountain Valley Facility”) pursuant to its obligations under the Amended and Restated Generation Interconnection Agreement between Public Service Company of Colorado and Fountain Valley Power, L.L.C., the Standard Large Generator Interconnection Agreement between Public Service Company of Colorado and Fountain Valley Power, L.L.C., or the successor to said agreement or agreements, at a price determined through the following pricing mechanism: Price = (Price per MWH * MWH) + Startup Charges Where: Price per MWH = [(price of natural gas delivered to Fountain Valley Facility in connection with power production) + Balancing Fees) * Heat Rate] + VOM Balancing Fees = any balancing fees or imbalance charges associated with delivery of natural gas to Fountain Valley Facility VOM = Variable operating and maintenance costs associated with power production Startup Charges = fixed charge of $9,500 per start per turbine All such sales of electric capacity or energy at wholesale shall be pursuant to Fountain Valley Power’s market-based rate wholesale power sales tariff on file with FERC.
